definitions.definition: To deny the existence, evidence, or truth of; to contradict .
examples: The investigation tending to negate any supernatural influences.

definitions.definition: To nullify or cause to be ineffective .
examples: Progress on the study has been negated by the lack of funds.
Persecution can be negated through exposure.

definitions.definition: To be negative ; bring or cause negative results.
To perform the NOT operation on.
